    {
      "id": "17b5a3d7-6a1c-42f3-b271-ea9a9babd336",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$0\\le f_n(x)\\le x^n$ et $f_n(1) = 1$ donc  lorsque $n\\to\\infty$ $f_n(x)\\to \\begin{cases}0 & \\text{ si }  x<1 \\cr 1 & \\text{ si }x=1.\\cr\\end{cases}$",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(0\\le f_n(x)\\le x^n\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f_n(1) = 1\\)</span> donc lorsque <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n\\to\\infty\\)</span> <span class=\"math inline\">\\(f_n(x)\\to \\begin{cases}0 &amp; \\text{ si }  x&lt;1 \\cr 1 &amp; \\text{ si }x=1.\\cr\\end{cases}\\)</span></p>\n"
      }
